summary: President's Intelligence Checklist from November 27, 1963, covering topics such as Cuban SAM site training, Syrian-Iraqi relations, Turkish political situation, Soviet agriculture and grain production, Communist China's wheat imports, Czechoslovakia-USSR relations, Cambodia's neutralization efforts, Egypt-Yemen conflict involving alleged poison gas use, Congolese political instability, and notes on South Korea, Venezuela, Indonesia-Philippines, Indonesia-Malaysia, Cuba, Cambodia, and USSR-US relations.
title: The President's Intelligence Checklist
